--- a/supabase/migrations/README.md
+++ b/supabase/migrations/README.md
@@ -11,6 +11,8 @@ Remote migrations applied to project `vzaceoipwimphdvdxcpa`:
 - `20260528215109_optimize_personalization_rls_initplan` — rewrites the policies above to use `(select auth.uid())` instead of `auth.uid()` so it is evaluated once per query (initPlan) rather than per row. Clears the `auth_rls_initplan` performance advisor; policy semantics are unchanged.
 - `20260530204343_grant_personalization_schema_access` — grants the base table/schema privileges on `recall.*` to `authenticated` + `service_role` (custom schemas don't inherit them; without this even the service role hit "permission denied for schema recall"). RLS still gates rows; `anon` is intentionally not granted.
 - `20260530204434_expose_recall_schema_to_api` — adds `recall` to the PostgREST exposed schemas (`pgrst.db_schemas`) so `supabase-js` `.schema("recall")` works. Also mirror `recall` in the dashboard (Settings → API → Exposed schemas) so the setting is durable.
+- `20260615120000_add_reminders_tables` — the user's reminders, captured in the native iOS entry form and synced here. `recall.reminders` holds the 16 scalar/relational "parts" (relational parts — tags, subtasks — live in `recall.reminder_tags` / `recall.reminder_subtasks` so they project to RDF/Neo4j edges). `seeded_from_template_id` links a reminder back into `recall.reminder_templates`. Completed reminders are **retained** (`status='completed'`). RLS: own-rows only `to authenticated` via `(select auth.uid())` (anonymous sign-in carries the `authenticated` role), with base grants to `authenticated` + `service_role`.
+- `20260615120001_harden_set_updated_at_search_path` — pins `recall.set_updated_at()`'s `search_path` to clear the `function_search_path_mutable` security advisor.
 
 The local Supabase CLI is not installed in this workspace, so these migrations were applied through the Supabase app connector and verified with SQL queries.
 
